." Man page for shell
.TH SIMPLE SHELL 1 "28 April 2023" "v1.0" "Simple Shell User Manual"
.SH NAME
Simple shell - A simple command line shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shell
.br
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B shell
is a simple command line shell that allows users to execute commands and built-in functions in a Unix-like environment. It is designed to provide basic functionality and ease of use.

.SH OPTIONS
There are no command line options available for the shell program.

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
The shell supports the following built-in commands:

.IP "cd"
Change the current working directory to the specified path.
.IP "exit"
Exit the shell, terminating the current session.
.IP "env"
Print the environment variables.

.SH USAGE
Launch the shell by running the shell executable. Once the shell is running, simply type in commands and press Enter to execute them. The shell will continue running until the exit command is entered or it is terminated by a signal.

.SH EXAMPLES
Change the current working directory to the /home/user directory:
.RS
.nf
$ cd /home/user
.fi
.RE

Display environment variables:
.RS
.nf
$ env
.fi
.RE

Exit the shell:
.RS
.nf
$ exit
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR dash (1),
.BR ksh (1),
.BR zsh (1)

.SH BUGS
The shell is a simple implementation and does not support many advanced features found in more complex shells. It may be less suitable for advanced users or complex scripting tasks.

.SH AUTHOR
The shell was developed by [Jose Alvarez & Giovanni Barreto]. Please report any bugs or issues to [6292@holbertonstudents.com].
